  "description": {
    "en-US": "Travel phrases for Singapore with audio, tuned for MRT directions, Grab rides, hawker-centre orders, hotel check-ins, and everyday cashless service conversations.",
    "zh-CN": "新加坡旅行短语卡，围绕 MRT、Grab、熟食中心点餐、酒店入住和无现金支付等高频服务场景整理。"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en-US": "Built for Singapore trips where English works often, but you still need fast, visible phrasing for hawker stalls, MRT routes, condo or mall drop-off points, and hotel or attraction counters. These cards are especially useful when the line is moving fast and you want to show the request instead of repeating it.",
    "zh-CN": "这套新加坡短语适合那种“英语大多能用，但现场节奏很快”的旅行场景，比如熟食中心点餐、MRT 换乘、商场或公寓下车点、酒店和景点柜台。排队很快时，直接给对方看短语卡往往比反复解释更高效。"
  },
  "teaser": {
    "en-US": "Built for Singapore MRT navigation, hawker-centre ordering, Grab pickups, and fast hotel or attraction counters.",
    "zh-CN": "适合新加坡 MRT、熟食中心点餐、Grab 上下车和酒店或景点柜台沟通。"
  },
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "English is common in Singapore, but short phrase cards still help in hawker centres, taxis, and busy counters where speed matters.",
      "Keep MRT station names, mall or tower addresses, and Grab pickup points easy to show because many destinations have multiple entrances.",
      "Dining phrases are most useful for hawker orders, takeaway requests, and simple food restrictions when the queue is moving quickly."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "在新加坡英语确实很常用，但在熟食中心、出租车和高峰柜台前，短语卡依然很适合用来加快沟通。",
      "MRT 站名、商场或办公楼地址、Grab 上车点最好提前准备好，因为很多目的地入口很多。",
      "餐饮短语最适合用在熟食中心点单、打包带走，以及快速说明饮食禁忌这些场景。"
    ]
  },
  "highlights": {
    "en-US": [
      "Hawker centres and MRT",
      "Grab rides and mall addresses",
      "Cashless payments and takeaway"
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "熟食中心与 MRT",
      "Grab 打车与商场地址",
      "无现金支付与打包带走"
    ]
  },
