  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Do I need phrase cards if I already speak English in Singapore?",
        "zh-CN": "如果我会英语，在新加坡还需要短语卡吗？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Yes, especially for hawker-centre orders, fast service counters, and showing precise destinations to drivers. The card is often faster than explaining the same request twice.",
        "zh-CN": "需要，尤其是在熟食中心点餐、快节奏柜台沟通，以及给司机确认具体下车点时。很多时候短语卡会比口头重复解释更快。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrase groups are most useful for Singapore?",
        "zh-CN": "在新加坡最常用的是哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport and dining. MRT, Grab, hawker centres, and hotel counters cover most first-day situations, then keep shopping and emergency phrases ready as backup.",
        "zh-CN": "优先准备交通和餐饮就很够用。MRT、Grab、熟食中心和酒店柜台能覆盖大多数第一天场景，再把购物和紧急求助类短语留作备用。"
      }
    }
  ]
}
